Two more people have appeared in court for the murder of 10-year-old Luyanda Msomi and his best friend, Njabulo Mankayi.ADVERTISINGinRead invented by Teads
Ali Yusaf, a 46-year-old Malawian, and Liziwe Ngwayishe, a 33-year-old woman from Clairwood, appeared made a brief appearance in the Durban Magistrate’s Court on Tuesday.
They face charges of murder, kidnapping and assault with intent to do grievous bodily harm.
They were remanded in custody until next week, when they will join co-accused Amahle Mawila – who appeared in court on Monday – in the dock.
READ: 'The person who did this killed my heart'
Njabulo and Luyanda disappeared on Thursday.













